On Mar 9, 2004, at 12:23 PM, Snoopy wrote:

> Also, I guess this is a 2 man job or is there a trick to get the nuts 
> back
> on the bolts that hold the shifter on.

A helper sure makes it a LOT easier.  You just need someone to hold the 
shifter steady while you thread the bolts and get them in place.  Then 
you can tap the backing plate with a mallet and screwdriver, with the 
not-quite-tight bolts providing some tension.

